        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Solar Water Pumping System&amp;quot; by the Renewable Energy Department, Government of Haryana, aims to encourage farmers and agriculture-based community groups to adopt clean and sustainable energy for irrigation by offering subsidized solar water pumping systems. It helps in improving agricultural productivity, reducing dependency on grid electricity or diesel, and promoting water-use efficiency through integration with micro-irrigation systems. Beneficiaries are eligible for a 75% subsidy on the installation of solar pumps.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n- **Subsidy Amount:** A 75% subsidy is provided on the cost of solar water pumps.\n",
        "exclusions_md": "\n- The applicant who has already availed benefits under any previous solar pump scheme is not eligible.\n\n<br>\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme \"Solar Water Pumping System\" by the Renewable Energy Department, Government of Haryana aims to encourage the adoption of renewable energy for irrigation. Through this scheme, solar water pumps are provided at a 75% subsidy to eligible farmers and institutions for irrigation need",
